text: Learned to row a boat away with just one finger Cast but prayers into the bow I hope I sink her Watch me fall asleep in a bag of rope If the storm comes back, cut my throat Calm the storm with all I must I must a-whimper  Cause I been holding out this hand I been holding out this hand Old sock money bank I spent all that I had Now we go round and around and around Oh, we go around and around and around  I cut the storm with just a stick to watch it splinter Now I’m begging ??? to make a home for winter Drew my children in the snow  And spilled my blood to watch them grow Cast me off this boat It’s me who sinks her  Cause I been holding out this hand I been holding out this hand Old sock money bank I spent all that I had Now we go round and around and around Oh, we go around and around and around Oh, we go around and around and around Oh, we go around and around and around
